stylometry: Price and Demand are dependant of each other. If Demand is high, price is high. Demand is low, then price is low. This is how businesses make money, take the oil companies for example, people need gas (demand) so the oil companies raise prices to make the most money possible. This will only change when people find an alternative source of fuel and gas is no longer needed in as large of quanity, which will drive the price of gas back down to a reasonable price. As a manager the descision needed to make would be how high to set prices? Well that depends on what the demand is for that product or service. I would set up a model by finding my break even point first then see how much of a similar product is selling for and how much of it is sold. From there i would determine my price in order to make the largest profit.
